\sqrt{n}
p,q
gcd(p,q) = 1
\sqrt{n} = \dfrac{p}{q}
\sqrt{n}
n = \dfrac{p}{q}\sqrt{n}
 \sqrt{n} = \dfrac{q *n}{p}
\sqrt{n} = \dfrac{p}{q}
 \sqrt{n} = \dfrac{q *n}{p}
 \dfrac{p}{q} = \dfrac{q *n}{p}
gcd(p,q) = 1
\frac{p}{q}
p,q,n
r
p*r = q*n
q *r = p
q*r = p
 r = \dfrac{p}{q} = \sqrt{n} \implies  r^2 = n
